## Migration Roadmap Phases (Draft)

### Phase 0: Discovery & Planning (Current)
- ✅ Read IDP documentation
- ⬜ Analyze RDM architecture and create service inventory
- ⬜ Document dependencies (service-to-service, databases, external systems)
- ⬜ Assess current containerization status
- ⬜ Initial WeS consultation
- ⬜ Select migration scenario (A, B, or C)
- ⬜ Create detailed migration plan

### Phase 1: Foundation Setup
- ⬜ Create RDM Cloud App Space
- ⬜ Onboard team (Azure AD groups, roles)
- ⬜ Setup GitLab.com repositories
- ⬜ Configure Artifactory repositories
- ⬜ Setup basic CI/CD pipeline (proof of concept)
- ⬜ Create non-prod environments (dev, int, rc)

### Phase 2: Pilot Migration
**Target: 1-2 low-risk, standalone services**
- ⬜ Containerize pilot service(s)
- ⬜ Setup CI/CD pipeline with IDP templates
- ⬜ Configure ArgoCD ApplicationSets
- ⬜ Migrate databases to PostgreSQL as a Service
- ⬜ Setup monitoring and logging
- ⬜ Deploy to dev/int environments
- ⬜ Test and validate
- ⬜ Document learnings and best practices
- ⬜ Deploy to rc/preprod/prod

### Phase 3: Iterative Migration
**Target: Remaining services in priority order**
- ⬜ Apply learnings from pilot
- ⬜ Migrate service groups incrementally
- ⬜ Update inter-service communication as needed
- ⬜ Migrate shared infrastructure (Kafka, schema registry)
- ⬜ Migrate common libraries (if needed)

### Phase 4: Completion
- ⬜ Migrate final services
- ⬜ Decommission old infrastructure
- ⬜ Full team training on IDP tools
- ⬜ Update documentation
- ⬜ Retrospective and knowledge sharing

